## Cincinnati PowerShell User Group – Pester testing with Matt McNabb

### When: June 20th – 6PM TUESDAY!

### Where: [Max Technical Training, Mason, OH](https://goo.gl/maps/ijBGbvJQR3B2)

### Sign up here: [Cincy PSUG Meetup](https://www.meetup.com/TechLife-Cincinnati/events/240208038/)

```powershell
PS C:\> Get-PSUG | where {$_.City -eq Cincinnati}
```

### *Pester testing with Matt McNabb*

Are you writing PowerShell scripts to manage production environments? Are you doing everything you can to protect those environments?  Pester is an open-source framework for testing PowerShell projects that will help you ensure your PowerShell project is production-ready. Come join us on June 20th at 6:00 PM to find out why and how you should be using Pester to test your PowerShell code, and more.

## Sponsor:

SAPIEN Technologies will be sponsoring the Cincinnati PowerShell User Group meeting and will be supplying the pizza!

